description: Enjoy Barcelona tapas with a twist! Ziryab's new location is in one of the oldest taverns of Barcelona at Carrer de Grunyi in an old maritime neighbourhood in medieval times. Its owners, a brother-sister duo, as well as Ziryab staff, can tell you many tales about the streets of the old city, and all they ask in return is interest, curiosity and a charming smile. The Ziryab concept is a blend of cultures. Its aim is to bring you the tastes of the Mediterranean, from herbs to spices to more specialised ingredients, while enjoying a wide variety of carefully selected wines from the wine-growing regions of the whole Mediterranean. Welcome to Ziryab and enjoy the quaintness and beauty of the location, the tasty flavours, our charming waitresses and the great variety of quality wines we have on offer. Celebrate your birthday, anniversary, group events or organise a wine tasting there.. Or just come alone and soak in the atmosphere. Ziryab has something for everyone.
localName: Ziryab bar de tapas fusión mediterránea

description: Lasarte Restaurant opened in January 2006 and holds 2 Michelin stars since 2010. Lasarte is Martín Berasategui's cuisine embassy in Barcelona. After a full renovation carried out recently, the new Lasarte Restaurant is surprisingly much more modern and with more spacious and bright look. The culinary offer keeps the essence of Martin Berasategui's cuisine. description: The Venue's notion is simple: old school elegant dishes using the finest ingredients prepared by our top chefs. The deceptively easy dishes earn their place with the choicest cuts of meat imported from Ireland. The vibe? Grown up, relaxed, playful. The setting? An opulent room you'll feel at home in, only better. In how many places can you get a perfectly cooked rib-eye steak with immaculate flavour, crisp triple cooked chunky chips? Notice the words "perfectly" and "immaculate". No, there are not many restaurants with the courage to deliver a menu based on the very sound theory that less is more; that a good kitchen is much better off cooking steak rather than mucking around with all manner of fashionable, cheffy malarkey. So, we take our hats off to our fantastic team, for helping us bring The Venue Sreakhouse to Barcelona. Come and join us at The Venue where there's always a warm welcome!
name: The Venue Steak House

description: Among the three hundred diners that fill this 30-year-old restaurant every day, you may spot the King of Spain, movie stars, and politicians. Botafumeiro has to be a well-oiled machine to keep all and sundry happy and coming back for more, and it does. The decor is so trad, with wood railings and banisters, white table linens, and nautically-themed art and objets. The menu focusses on the sea, try fruits de mer for two to start, followed by anglerfish fisherman's stew with white beams or one of the barbecued fish, then a dessert of Belgian chocolate volcano with chocolate sherbet. Wine list is an ambassador for Spanish wines.
name: Botafumeiro

description: When you step out of the high-tech lift into the lobby of the Torre d'Alta Mar, 75 metres above the sea, you just may have an out-of-body moment. The 360 degree view is that spectacular, the sea and the city at your feet, the encircling hills in the distance. It has certainly attracted its share of architects, actors, and artists. But this high-end, luxury restaurant does everything in its power to distract you. The fittings are elegant and modern, the Catalan food (emphasis on fish) with its international influences right up there with the standards expected of a restaurant in Barcelona now. Dishes include starter of cod and lobster envelopes with black olive oil and mixed veg and main course of seabass with sauteed greens, shiitake, rice noodles, soya and sesame. Wines and service are very good, too. Remember to request a table by the window!
name: Torre d'Alta Mar

description: Situated near Barcelona's bustling main streets, Arcano is a culinary gem housed in a charming 17th-century building. What sets us apart is our dedication to the art of charcoal oven cooking. This ancient method infuses each dish with a distinctive smoky flavor that leaves a lasting impression. Our menu is a celebration of this tradition, featuring a diverse range of dishes. From the crispness of fresh vegetables to the tenderness of succulent meats and the delicacy of perfectly prepared fish, every bite tells a story of craftsmanship and flavor. As you explore the vibrant streets of Barcelona, don't miss the opportunity to experience this unique culinary journey. Arcano promises not just a meal, but a taste of history and tradition.
name: Arcano Restaurant

description: Carballeira is an emblematic restaurant that, since 1944 has been offering the best fresh seafood delivered daily from Galicia.Located in Barceloneta district, a few steps from the sea and right in front of Port Vell, Carballeira has maintained from its beginning, the essence of one of the most popular and authentic seafood restaurants in town.Local waiters with years of experience ensure an excellent service.Delectable seafood carefully selected. Delicious rices: with lobster, "a banda" or black with cuttlefish. Line-caught fish, succulent dishes of monkfish, bass, turbot or hake. And for meat lovers a good T-bone steak or a Galician Veal entrecote. A wide selection of dishes to please every taste.SPECIAL SERVICES • Private dining rooms with natural light inside for groups of 10-40 people. Group menus, also customizable.• All day dining service from 13h to 24h, to dine at your leisure.
name: Carballeira

description: ALİ OCAKBAŞI Redesigning the fireside cuisine, a key element of Anatolian food and beverage culture with a novel understanding, Ali Ocakbaşı aims to offer a new generation fireside and kebab pleasure in the most iconic locations of Istanbul. The restaurant appreciates the bounty of local farms and seasonality, preparing local flavors with original recipes through modern presentations. Ali Ocakbaşı offers its guests unique flavors with the most natural aromas grilled on the fireside or in wood fire ovens. Cooperating with family breeding farms, the restaurant focuses on sustainability by supporting the geographically marked endemic species of the region. Every year, it contributes to reforestation as much as the carbon footprint of its brand. Ali Ocakbaşı aspires to the best tastes and the most enjoyable gourmet experience. With a qualified team and a great menu filled with classic, eclectic, and inventive fare, the restaurant continues to welcome local and foreign guests who want to spend every moment of the day in its branches located in Gümüşsuyu, Kuruçeşme, Karaköy and Suadiye where they will enjoy the city. Ali Ocakbaşı offers this unique gastronomy experience also in Europe, with its branch in Amsterdam. Now we are coming to Barcelona.
name: Ali OcakbasI
